# {{appName}}

Expo (React Native) app built on `simplix-react-native` — expo-router navigation, NativeWind styling, and the shared domain packages of this workspace.

## Run

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm --filter {{#if scope}}{{scope}}/{{/if}}{{appName}} start
```

- `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL` — API origin (defaults to `http://localhost:8080`). Android emulators reach the host machine at `http://10.0.2.2:8080`.
- `EXPO_PUBLIC_ENABLE_MOCKS=true` — run against msw/native mock handlers instead of a live API.

## Structure

```
app/                expo-router routes (screens own their headers via Stack.Screen)
src/bootstrap/            boot wiring (mutator, query client, i18n, mocks)
src/locales/        app-level translations (common namespace)
```

Screens compose `@simplix-react-native/ui` (Screen, Section, EntityList, FormFields, DetailFields); domain data comes from the workspace `domain-*` packages through their generated hooks. Entity screen sets are generated with:

```bash
simplix scaffold <entity> --native --module <module> --app {{appName}}
```
